I would wire it right from the solenoid.. to a 6 volt relay.. that way you wont
have to run the large supply wire to a switch... any electronics repair place
or auto electronics place can supply to with the stuff and how to do it if ya
ask em nicely. and with using a good relay you are not gonna have any voltage
drop that you get when running a long power wire to the dash and then back to
the pump... Also you can use a smaller switch or even tie it into a switched
power source on your ignition switch or fuse panel.. and yes always put a fuse
inline...

